1.At each iteration, pick the remaining request with the fewest number of conflicts with other remaining requests (breaking ties arbitrarily). sai

2. Schedule the requests in increasing order of deadline dj
3. T must be a minimum spanning tree but P may not be a shortest s-t path.
4. A minimum bottleneck spanning tree is not always a minimum spanning tree, but a minimum spanning tree is always a minimum bottleneck spanning tree.
5. For every G and H, these edges are contained in some minimum spanning tree of H